South Africa middle-distance runner and Olympic gold medalist, Caster Semenya is reportedly ready to be a parent.A source has revealed to Drum magazine that Caster and her wife Violet Raseboya have been talking about raising a family together. They are definitely ready to be parents. It s a talk they have been having for years and it s the next level of their union, the source told Drum.Another sources confirmed the news to the publication. Caster and Violet are amazing people and they would make great parents, the source said.